  "title": "REINFORCING IRON WORKER",
  "description": "<p>• Reading blueprints or looking at sketches to determine how to install rebar or mesh</p><p>• Figuring out the quantity, size, and shapes of reinforcing rods and determining where to place them</p><p>• Preparing rebar and mesh for installation using metal shears, hacksaws, and torches</p><p>• Bending or welding rebar together</p><p>• Installing cables</p><p>• Using pliers to tie wire around rods to fasten them together</p><p>• Positioning and securing rods, cables, mesh, or rebar in concrete forms</p><p></p>",
